==English==

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*ten-}}
First attested around 1380. From {{inh|en|enm|absteynen}}, {{m|enm|absteinen}}, {{m|enm|abstenen}}, from {{der|en|fro|astenir}}, {{m|fro|abstenir}}, from {{der|en|la|abstineō||to hold oneself back}} from {{m|la|abs-||from}} + {{m|la|teneō||I hold}}. See also {{m|en|tenable}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/əbˈsteɪn/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/əbˈsteɪn/|/æbˈsteɪn/}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-abstain.wav|Audio (UK)}}
* {{rhymes|en|eɪn|s=2}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive|reflexive|obsolete}} Keep or withhold oneself. {{defdate|Attested from around 1350 to 1470 until the mid 16<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=9}}</ref>
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} [[refrain|Refrain]] from (something or doing something); keep from doing, especially an [[indulgence]]. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#: {{ux|en|In order to improve his health, Rob decided to '''abstain''' from smoking.}}
#* '''22 May 1948''', United Nations, ''Security Council Resolution 49''
#*:The Security Council {{...}} calls upon all Governments and authorities, without prejudice to the rights, claims or positions of the parties concerned, to '''abstain''' from any hostile military action in Palestine and to that end to issue a cease-fire order to their military and paramilitary forces
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1597|passage=Who '''abstains''' from meat that is not gaunt?|author=Shakespeare|title=Richard II|section=II-i}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive|obsolete}} [[fast|Fast]] {{gloss|not eat for a period}}. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} Deliberately refrain from casting one's [[vote]] at a meeting where one is present. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED/>
